<section id="validate-html" class="block-content bg-white">
	<h2>Validate your HTML file</h2>
	<p>To check your <b>contact.html</b> file is correct, use the official W3C Markup Validation Service. Follow these steps.</p>
	<ol>
		<li>Go to this web page: <a href="https://validator.w3.org" target="_blank">https://validator.w3.org</a>.</li>
		<li>Click the <b>Validate by Direct Input</b> tab.
		<IMG SRC="assets/img/validate-html.png" class="img-fluid" ALT="Project Contact"></li>
		<li>Copy and paste your <b>contact.html</b> file into the box named <b>Enter the Markup to validate</b>.</li>
		<li>Click the <b>Check</b> button.</li>
		<li>If you see any errors, return to your <b>contact.html</b> file in Sublime Text, fix the errors, save the file, and copy the entire file again.<span class="inside-ol">&nbsp;</span>
		In the HTML Validator, click the <b>Back</b> button of your web browser to again display the <b>Validate by Direct Input</b> tab. Click once in the tab and paste in your corrected HTML file. Your new, pasted-in file will replace the earlier version. Finally, click the <b>Check</b> button.</li>
	</ol>
</section>

